<h3>Signs of a Crawl Budget Problem</h3>
<ul>
<li>New pages take weeks to get indexed instead of days</li>
<li>Google Search Console shows "Discovered - currently not indexed" for large numbers of URLs</li>
<li>Crawl Stats report shows Google spending most of its time on low-value pages</li>
<li>Important pages have not been recrawled in 30+ days</li>
<li>XML sitemap shows pages that are not in the Google index</li>
</ul>
<p>If your pages get indexed within 1 to 3 days of publishing, your crawl budget is fine. Focus your time on content and links instead.</p>
